# Zholda / Zhetisay Bus — Cursor Rules

## Project
Real-time PWA bus tracker for Zhetisay, Kazakhstan. React 19 + TypeScript + Vite. See CONTEXT.md for full context.

## Stack constraints
- React 19, Tailwind v4 (@tailwindcss/vite — no postcss config), Leaflet/react-leaflet v5
- Supabase JS v2 for DB + Realtime. No auth library — drivers use PIN only.
- No Redux/Zustand. All state lives in App.tsx via useState/useCallback.
- All UI text must go through i18n.ts (KZ/RU/EN). Never hardcode user-facing strings.

## Code style
- TypeScript strict. No `any`. Prefer discriminated unions over nullable returns.
- Functional components only. No class components.
- Tailwind for layout/spacing. Inline `style={}` for dynamic colors (route colors, etc.).
- Keep components focused. Heavy logic goes in hooks under src/hooks/.
- No comments that just restate what the code does. Only explain non-obvious intent.

## Map / geo rules
- Leaflet uses [lat, lng]. GeoJSON uses [lng, lat]. Never mix them up.
- haversineMeters() and snapToRoute() expect { lat, lng } objects.
- Route GeoJSON coordinates in mockData.ts are [lng, lat] per GeoJSON spec.
- snapToRoute() snaps within ~50m. Beyond that it returns raw GPS — this is intentional.

## GPS / Safari
- navigator.geolocation.watchPosition() MUST be called synchronously in startWatching().
  Never put an await before it — Safari requires it in the user-gesture call stack.
- GPS error code 1 = PERMISSION_DENIED → stop session. Codes 2/3 are transient → keep watching.

## Supabase
- vehicles table columns: id, bus_number, latitude, longitude, last_updated, is_active, driver_pin
- authenticateDriver() returns AuthResult (discriminated union: ok / wrong_pin / already_active).
- bus_number matches route id/number in mockData.ts. Keep them in sync.

## PWA
- Icons needed: /public/pwa-192.png, /public/pwa-512.png, /public/apple-touch-icon.png (not yet created).
- display: standalone. Safe-area insets applied via env(safe-area-inset-top/bottom).
- (display-mode: standalone) = running as installed PWA. Use this to branch onboarding logic.